# DIGITAL SALES ROOMS
# =============================================================================
CATEGORY_CONTENT["digital-sales-rooms"] = {
 "definition": "provide shared online workspaces where sellers and buyers collaborate on content, track deal progress, and keep every stakeholder aligned throughout the buying process.",
 "definition_expanded": "Digital sales rooms replace the back-and-forth email chains and scattered attachments that define most B2B buying experiences. Sellers create a branded workspace for each deal, populate it with proposals, case studies, pricing, and next steps, then share a single link with the buying committee. Every stakeholder accesses the same materials, comments in one place, and the seller sees exactly who viewed what and when. For complex deals with 5-10 stakeholders spread across departments, a DSR reduces the friction that causes deals to stall in committee review.",
 "buying_guide": "Consider how many stakeholders are involved in your typical deal. Digital sales rooms add the most value in multi-threaded enterprise deals where 4-10 buyers need to review materials, share internally, and align on a decision. For deals with a single decision-maker and a short cycle, a DSR adds process overhead without proportional benefit. If your average deal involves three or more people on the buyer side, the engagement visibility alone justifies the investment.\n\nContent analytics are the hidden value. Every DSR shows you who opened the room. The best ones show you which pages each stakeholder spent time on, whether they forwarded the link to someone new, and when engagement dropped off. This buyer intent data tells you where deals are progressing and where they have gone silent. Dock and Aligned excel at this engagement tracking. Evaluate how granular the analytics are before choosing.\n\nBranding and customization matter for enterprise sellers. A digital sales room that looks like a polished extension of your brand creates a different impression than a generic shared folder. Templates let reps spin up professional rooms in minutes without design skills. Mutual action plans keep both sides accountable to timelines. Look for tools that balance ease-of-setup with enough customization to match your sales motion and brand standards.",
 "faqs": [
 {"question": "What is a digital sales room?", "answer": "A digital sales room is a shared online workspace where a seller organizes all deal-related content, including proposals, case studies, pricing, demo recordings, and next steps, in one branded space. Buyers access it via a single link, and sellers track engagement across every stakeholder. It replaces the scattered email attachments and shared drives that most B2B deals rely on."},
 {"question": "How do digital sales rooms help close deals faster?", "answer": "DSRs reduce deal friction in three ways. They centralize all materials so buyers stop losing attachments. They provide mutual action plans that keep both sides accountable to timelines. And they give sellers visibility into buyer engagement, so reps know when a deal is progressing and when it needs intervention. Teams using DSRs report 10-20% shorter deal cycles on average."},
 {"question": "Are digital sales rooms worth it for small deals?", "answer": "For deals under $10K with a single buyer and a short cycle, a DSR adds process without proportional value. The category is built for complex B2B deals with multiple stakeholders, long evaluation periods, and significant content exchange. If your typical deal involves 3+ people reviewing materials over 30+ days, a DSR earns its cost quickly."},
 {"question": "How much do digital sales rooms cost?", "answer": "Pricing ranges from free tiers with limited rooms (Flowla, Trumpet) to $40-$80/user/month for full-featured platforms (Dock, Aligned). GetAccept bundles DSR functionality with e-signatures and proposals at higher price points. Most tools price per user with unlimited rooms, though some charge per room or per deal."},
 {"question": "Can digital sales rooms integrate with my CRM?", "answer": "Yes. All major DSR tools integrate with Salesforce and HubSpot, syncing room activity and engagement data to deal records. The best integrations update CRM fields automatically when buyers view content or complete mutual action plan steps. This engagement data enriches pipeline visibility without requiring reps to log activities manually."},
 ],
}

